<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    The candy fans can
 &HT;    c. 2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   LAS VEGAS _ M&AMP;M's World is one of the most popular stops on the
Strip. And the most popular stop in the store is the Colorworks
wall made up of see-through tubes of M&AMP;Ms in 21 colors made only
for this store and one in New York City. Nearly everyone leaves
with an $8-a-pound bag. For fans of the candy that debuted in 1941,
the store sells 3,000 logo items with an entire section devoted to
No. 36 Ernie Irvan M&AMP;M Racing NASCAR souvenirs. The store reports
that half of all sales are to tourists from Japan. The $3 M&AMP;M's
Academy shows you how the candy is made and includes a 20-minute
3-D show starring Red and Yellow M&AMP;Ms.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
