<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-01-27 11:39 </DATE_TIME>
<HEADER>
A8021 &Cx1f; tad-z
r t BC-TRAVEL-VEGASMEET28-CO     01-27 0168
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-TRAVEL-VEGASMEET28-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Meet you in Vegas
 &HT;    c. 2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   Las Vegas is out to be the world convention/ trade-show capital,
which means hosting everything from the mega-moneymakers, such as
the COMDEX computer show, to meetings that scream obscure, bizarre
or there'd-better-be-an-open-bar boring. Here are some:
</P>
<P>
   _ Exotic Dancer Fan Fair
</P>
<P>
   _ Self Storage Association
</P>
<P>
   _ May 97 Moms
</P>
<P>
   _ Soldier of Fortune magazine
</P>
<P>
   _ Returned Peace Corps Volunteers/El Salvador
</P>
<P>
   _ U.S. Department of Defense
</P>
<P>
   _ American Concrete Pipe Association
</P>
<P>
   _ Driving School Association of the Americas
</P>
<P>
   _ National Chrysanthemum Society
</P>
<P>
   _ National Association of Reunion Managers
</P>
<P>
   _ American Ostrich Association _ International Haircolor
Exchange
</P>
<P>
   _ Quiet Birdmen
</P>
<P>
   _ Institute of Internal Auditors
</P>
<P>
   Source: Las Vegas Convention and Visitors Authority 1999-2000
calendar
</P>
