<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-TRAVEL-VEGASESCORTS28-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Escort services paper the Strip with advertising
 &HT;    By Paul Lomartire
 &HT;    c. 2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   LAS VEGAS _ ``Prostitution is pretty blatant in town here,''
says Lt. Terry Davis of the Las Vegas Metropolitan Police vice
squad. Last year, the 22-member vice unit made about 5,000 arrests.
</P>
<P>
   Prostitution is legal in some parts of Nevada _ the closest to
Las Vegas is about 50 miles west in the town of Pahrump.
Prostitution in Vegas is high-profile because the sidewalks
fronting billion-dollar hotels are crowded with
minimum-wage-earning Mexicans recruited to hand out papers, cards
and slick magazines advertising escort services.
</P>
<P>
   Three men run a majority of Vegas' 140 escort services, Davis
says. These ``escorts'' frequently are hookers, he adds.
</P>
<P>
   ``The problem is 90-some percent of them will proposition you
for sex because that's how they make their money.''
</P>
<P>
   Clark County passed an anti-handbill ordinance that was ruled
unconstitutional by Nevada's Ninth Circuit Court of Appeals. The
county is trying to come up with another law. But eliminating the
sidewalk handouts won't solve the prostitution epidemic. Telephone
yellow pages list more than 100 escort service ads, and then
there's the Internet Web sites.
</P>
<P>
   The biggest problem for police is that customers who are ripped
off rarely report it, for obvious reasons.
</P>
<P>
   ``There are people that have been robbed, stabbed and all kinds
of things that you can't imagine by engaging in this high-risk
activity.''
</P>
<P>
   Summon an ``escort,'' says Davis, and this is frequently what
happens:
</P>
<P>
   ``The girl will come up to the room, and she'll say, 'You owe
$125 and that's just the service fee. That will allow me to dance
for you for up to an hour.' Up to an hour means maybe one minute.
</P>
<P>
   ``Once they get that money, then they say, 'Anything beyond
that, I work for tips.' 'What do you mean by that?' Then you play
the word game, and ultimately they solicit you for an act of sex
for a fee, which ends up being another $300, $400, $500, maybe
$1,000.''
</P>
<P>
   But it can be a lot worse than just losing money.
</P>
<P>
   ``A lot of times what they'll do, these girls will come up to
your room and drug you, put something in your drink,'' reports
Davis. ``Once you're knocked out, off they go with all your jewelry
and money. That happens on quite a few occasions. It's called a
drug-induced-trick-roll.''
</P>
<P>
   For most tourists, the closest they've come to a Las Vegas
hooker is seeing actress Elisabeth Shue play one in the film
Leaving Las Vegas.
</P>
<P>
   Are there any Vegas prostitutes that look like Shue?
</P>
<P>
   ``There are some very good-looking girls that are working for
the (escort) services, some that are freelancing,'' says Davis, who
saw the movie.
</P>
<P>
   Any like Elisabeth Shue?
</P>
<P>
   ``I've never seen one,'' reports Davis.
</P>
<P>
   Paul Lomartire writes for the Palm Beach Post, West Palm Beach,
Fla.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
