<P>
   STYLE-MAKEUPSALON _ Caren Stearns is a girly-girl and she's not
afraid to admit it. ``You could live in here,'' the 24-year old
office manager said on a recent make-up outing to new salon
superstore Ulta. ``It's more female oriented.'' With the cosmetic
and beauty industry racking up over $40 billion in U.S. sales in
1998, the new breed of salon is trying to be everything to every
woman. No longer content with cutting and styling hair, salons have
branched out _ with everything from pantyhose and condoms to home
furnishings and coffeetable fountains. (Poe, Austin
American-Statesman) MOVED
</P>
<P>
   FASHION-MACKIE _ Bob Mackie can work fashion miracles with
tulle, chiffon, bugle beads and pearls. And though pieces from his
romantic spring collection won't magically endow you with the
outlandish style of Cher (whom he has designed for extensively) or
the bodacious bod of Barbie (for whom he also creates
out-of-this-world looks), they can make you feel pretty darn close
to princess-like. The 60-year-old designer recently visited Saks
Fifth Avenue on Palm Beach to show off shapely Mackie gowns, shake
hands with longtime admirers and sign autographs for Barbie
collectors. Before he greeted fans, we grabbed him for a quick chat
in a Saks fitting room. (Sturrock, Palm Beach Post). 17. MOVED
</P>
<P>
   FASHION-POSTMENOPAUSE _ New clothing line takes into account
post-menopausal changes in women's bodies. (Waco Tribune-Herald).
35. WITH PHOTOS. MOVED
</P>
<P>
   SEASONAL-WEAR _ WACO, Texas _ There's a slight chill in the air
in the morning, but by afternoon the sun can get a little too warm,
and the evening air can be downright chilly. With the weather doing
wacky things this time of year, what's a gal or guy to wear?
(Kincheloe, Waco Tribune-Herald) MOVED
</P>
