<P>
   SUNDANCE _ From the Sundance Film Festival. A ``you are there''
look at independent movies from America's premiere fest. This is
the place that bred ``sex, lies &AMP; videotape,'' ``Hoop Dreams,''
``Boys Don't Cry'' and ``The Blair Witch Project.'' It's a 10-day
festival (it concludes Jan. 30) and our color story provides the
eyes and ears from all viewpoints: the tattooed twentysomething
selling espresso from a crowded Starbucks; the hopeful filmmaker
publicizing his movie with a crude cardboard sign that reads:
``Help. I need a distributor;'' and the film industry types who ski
and talk on cell phones at the same time Keys to the final weekend
of the festival, that concludes on Super Bowl Sunday. (BLongino,
Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 40.
</P>
<P>
   EDs: Embargoed for Sunday, Jan. 30.
</P>
