<DATE_TIME> 2000-01-27 11:45 </DATE_TIME>
<HEADER>
A8034 &Cx1f; tad-z
r l BC-SEASONAL-WEAR28-COX     01-27 0634
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-SEASONAL-WEAR28-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Between seasons, fashion gets down to basics
 &HT;    By Amy Kincheloe
 &HT;    c. 2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   WACO, Texas _ There's a slight chill in the air in the morning,
but by afternoon the sun can get a little too warm, and the evening
air can be downright chilly.
</P>
<P>
   With the weather doing wacky things this time of year, what's a
gal or guy to wear?
</P>
<P>
   ``Anything you can layer on in the morning and take off as the
day gets warmer,'' said Duke Nelson, a store manager of the Gap.
``That also makes it perfect for night (because you can put the
layers back on as it gets cooler).''
</P>
<P>
   Nelson suggests layering different pieces of clothing to help
get through this transitional time between holiday and spring
fashions.
</P>
<P>
   ``Transitional times are really tough because it's hard to find
something that's not going to be too heavy or too light,'' Nelson
said. ``But it's a true test of your wardrobe, because if you have
a lot of the basics, you'll be fine.''
</P>
<P>
   But what are a few of the basics?
</P>
<P>
   ``Khakis are perfect for spring,'' Nelson said. ``They have a
more freer style than jeans, and they're also lighter-weight.''
</P>
<P>
   For women, Nelson suggests basics such as khakis, twin sets and
matte jersey dresses.
</P>
<P>
   ``With those basics, you can totally go through the transition
to spring without a problem,'' Nelson said.
</P>
<P>
   For men, Nelson suggests fine-gauge sweaters and plain front
khakis, which can be dressed up or down depending of the type of
shirt worn.
</P>
<P>
   Carol Gilliland, manager of the Buckle store in Waco, Texas,
said she has also seen a lot of people wearing basic attire during
this transitional time.
</P>
<P>
   ``A lot of people are wearing long-sleeved T-shirts under
short-sleeved T-shirts,'' Gilliland said. ``That's a lot of what we
are layering in the store. It's becoming a pretty big look.''
</P>
<P>
   Gilliland said many people are choosing to wear a colored
T-shirt with detailing on it with a plain white long-sleeved
T-shirt underneath or a plain, colored T-shirt paired with a
colored, long-sleeved T-shirt with detailing on the sleeves.
</P>
<P>
   ``I also think short-sleeved woven shirts over long-sleeved
T-shirts look great,'' Gilliland said. ``It's casual, but it looks
cool.''
</P>
<P>
   With not quite cold but not quite hot weather, Gilliland said
people are still interested in lightweight sweatshirts and
sweaters.
</P>
<P>
   ``We've had a lot of people come in looking for them, and we've
almost sold out of the lightweight sweaters,'' Gilliland said.
</P>
<P>
   And even though Gilliland's store is starting to sell shorts,
there haven't been many early buyers, she said.
</P>
<P>
   ``People haven't started wearing shorts just yet, but I have
noticed girls wearing pedal pushers.''
</P>
<P>
   Nelson said the colors of this in-between time differ from
winter and spring.
</P>
<P>
   ``I think people are tired of (winter) darks and (holiday)
brights, and they're looking for something lighter,'' Nelson said.
``Anything that's lighter and takes away the heaviness of their
clothing.''
</P>
<P>
   And since basic clothing in basic colors is probably your best
bet during these transitional weeks, now is the time to find them.
</P>
<P>
   ``A lot of stores are in 'sale' mode and now is a good time to
get those basic transitional pieces to carry you through to
spring,'' Gilliland said.
</P>
<P>
   Here are a few transition basics to hold you over until spring:
</P>
<P>
   _ Khakis
</P>
<P>
   _ Twin sets
</P>
<P>
   _ Tank tops
</P>
<P>
   _ Cardigans
</P>
<P>
