George W. Bush say, through his perma-smirk, that his victory in
Iowa marked
</P>
<P>
   ``the beginning of the end of the Clinton era.`` I'm going to
miss that old boy. If Clinton is replaced by the son of a Bush he
beat in 1992, I'm going to miss him an awful lot. We can't go back
to a Bush, a lesser one at that. By ROB MORSE.
