   &UR; STATE OF THE UNION &LR;  (``w'' code)
</P>
<P>
   The New York Times plans four pages of stories, photos, graphics
and text on President Clinton's State of The Union address. The
speech begins at 9 p.m. EST; the longest of his previous addresses
was 81 minutes.
</P>
