<P>
   MUSIC-CLUB (Los Angeles) _ Music executive Jim Griffin was
disgusted at the way people in the industry didn't help each other.
So he started an informal club at a seedy Vietnamese restaurant in
Los Angeles' Chinatown. Now every Sunday, music moguls, Internet
entrepreneurs, venture capitalists and recent college graduates
slurp noodle soup, swap ideas, and cut deals. By Lynda Gorov. 1150
words. (a and e coding)
</P>
<P>
   PARISH-NURSING (Westborough, Mass.) _ As the number of priests
and nuns available to visit the sick declines, and as HMOs cut
costs by reducing hospital stays, churches are hiring nurses. It's
an idea that began in Chicago 20 years ago, was recognized by the
American Nurses Association two years ago. By Michael Paulson. 1550
words. PHOTO
</P>
