   US-ELIAN _ MIAMI _ In the aftermath, and fallout, of the meeting
between 6-year-old Cuban rafter Elian Gonzalez and his
grandmothers, U.S. Attorney General Janet Reno and the Miami Beach
nun she charged with overseeing the meeting were singing from two
different books Thursday. The U.S. Justice Department filed motions
in court to stop the Miami family's lawsuit. And, the grandmothers
and Elian's Miami relatives return to Washington to further plead
their cases to Congress. Developing. (MWilliams, Cox News Service).
</P>
