<P>
   ISRAEL-BARAK _ JERUSALEM _ In the first scandal to hit his
administration, Ehud Barak is faulted in a government report for
gross violations of campaign laws by his political party during the
elections. Israeli Attorney General Eliakim Rubenstein Thursday
ordered a criminal investigation into Barak's fundraising _ and the
fundraising of four other parties. Barak, a man who prides himself
on his attention to detail, said he did not know what was taking
place inside his own campaign. (Kaplow, Cox News Service).
