<P>
   RUSSIA-LAUNDER (Dateline to kum) _ A Swiss court issues a
summons for Pavel Borodin, a former aide to Yeltsin (head of
Kremlin property office), in connection with its money laundering
inquiry.
</P>
<P>
   RUSSIA-POLITICS (Moscow) _ Reformist groups say they'll end
their boycott of parliament, which was prompted by Acting President
Putin's alliance with the Communists. By Celestine Bohlen.
</P>
