   INTERNATIONAL
</P>
<P>
   (Will move in ``i'' news file.)
</P>
<P>
   ISRAEL-FUNDRAISING (Jerusalem) _ Prime Minister Ehud Barak's
party was fined and placed under criminal investigation Thursday
after the state comptroller issued a blistering account of its
alleged violations of campaign finance laws during the 1999
elections. The comptroller, Eliezer Goldberg, did not implicate
Barak personally but he held him accountable for what he described
as a ``trampling of the law'' by his One Israel party. Barak's
associates circumvented strict campaign finance restrictions
systematically, channeling illegal contributions into a host of
non-profit organizations, the comptroller said. By Deborah Sontag.
</P>
<P>
   With photo.
</P>
