in line for succession when his friend of 35 years retires.
Offensive coordinator Mike Martz has been promised the head job, in
writing. That's fine with White, who was given a two-year contract
extension that mirrors the length of Vermeil's commitment.
</P>
<P>
   ``When I came here, I had no designs on being a head coach
anymore, especially at the NFL level,'' White said. ``I've had my
place in the sun.''
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-01-27-00 1716EST &QL; 
</TRAILER>
