 &HT;    COX NEWS SERVICE SPORTS BUDGET
 &HT;    c. 2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   These sports stories for release Friday, January 28, 2000, are
moving today to clients of the New York Times News Service.
</P>
<P>
   If you have questions or need a resend, please call CoxNet, the
Cox News Service, at 404-526-5456.
</P>
<P>
   SUPER BOWL COVERAGE
</P>
<P>
   FBN-SBOWL-COLD _ ATLANTA _ Atlanta is expected to bid in March
for the 2005 or 2006 Super Bowl, but NFL guru Jim Steeg said on
Wednesday that it would be up to the 33 owners to decide whether
the area is ``too cold'' to get another bid. We poll as many NFL
owners and officials as possible to determine how this cold and
disastrous week has affected the city's chances. (Staff, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). 22.
</P>
<P>
   FBN-SBOWL-SAFETY _ ATLANTA _ Have pro football players become so
big, so fast that they have outgrown safety measures? Certainly,
the collisions have become increasingly violent during the 1990s.
We let the experts discuss the physical changes in players,
physical changes in equipment and what we can expect in the future.
