<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-01-27 19:49 </DATE_TIME>
<HEADER>
A8585 &Cx1f; tad-z
u d BC-SUPERBOWL-DIPS-RECIPE     01-27 1091
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-SUPERBOWL-DIPS-RECIPES28-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Dips help make football game festive
 &HT;    By Jan Norris
 &HT;    c. 2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   WEST PALM BEACH, Fla. _ Here are dips to give your Super Bowl
party a winning edge.
</P>
<P>
   BROCCOMOLE
</P>
<P>
   1large head of broccoli
</P>
<P>
   1/2teaspoon fresh ground cumin
</P>
<P>
   1/2teaspoon fresh ground cilantro
</P>
<P>
   Juice of 1/2 lemon
</P>
<P>
   1/2teaspoon crushed garlic (or to taste) 1/2teaspoon finely
chopped shallots (or to taste)
</P>
<P>
   1medium tomato, roughly diced
</P>
<P>
   Steam broccoli in microwave (8 minutes on high power, or until
easily pierced with fork) or on stovetop.
</P>
<P>
   Cut up broccoli into chunks and place in food processor with
remaining ingredients except tomato. Process until consistency of
guacamole; mixture should have small chunks. Stir in tomato and
adjust seasonings to taste.
</P>
<P>
   Makes approximately 4 cups.
</P>
<P>
   (Recipe from Internet recipes site, www.vegweb.com)
ROMESCO-STYLE ROASTED RED PEPPER DIP
</P>
<P>
   2yellow bell peppers, halved
</P>
<P>
   2red bell peppers, halved
</P>
<P>
   8large whole garlic cloves, unpeeled
</P>
<P>
   12almonds
</P>
<P>
   1tablespoon olive oil
</P>
<P>
   1teaspoon sherry wine vinegar or red wine vinegar
</P>
<P>
   Cayenne pepper to taste
</P>
<P>
   Preheat broiler. Line heavy large baking sheet with foil.
Arrange peppers cut side down in center of baking sheet; surround
with garlic. Broil 6 inches from heat until peppers are blackened
and garlic is tender, about 12 minutes. Note: Turn garlic often.
</P>
<P>
   Gather foil up around peppers and garlic; let stand until cool
enough to handle, about 10 minutes.
</P>
<P>
   Working over bowl to catch juices, peel and seed peppers;
reserve juices. Peel and chop garlic, discarding any hard pieces.
</P>
<P>
   Finely chop 6 almonds in food processor. Add peppers and
remaining ingredients. Process until smooth. Chill or serve at room
temperature.
</P>
<P>
   Makes 1 1/4 cups.
</P>
<P>
   (Recipe from Richard Sax and Marie Simmons, Bon Appetit, June
1993.)
</P>
<P>
   DELUXE SALMON SPREAD
</P>
<P>
   1pound cooked salmon
</P>
<P>
   1cup mayonnaise
</P>
<P>
   2tablespoons green peppers, diced
</P>
<P>
   2tablespoons green onions, thinly sliced
</P>
<P>
   2tablespoons pimiento, diced
</P>
<P>
   2teaspoons lemon juice
</P>
<P>
   1teaspoon tarragon vinegar
</P>
<P>
   1teaspoon horseradish
</P>
<P>
   1teaspoon chopped dried dillweed
</P>
<P>
   Put mayonnaise, pepper and pimiento into blender on low until
smooth. Put mixture into mixing bowl and add remaining ingredients.
Mix well. Chill before serving.
</P>
<P>
   Makes approximately 3 cups.
</P>
<P>
   PEPPERONI PIZZA DIP
</P>
<P>
   8ounces cream cheese, softened
</P>
<P>
   1/2cup sour cream
</P>
<P>
   1teaspoon oregano
</P>
<P>
   1/8teaspoon garlic powder
</P>
<P>
   1/8teaspoon red pepper flakes, crushed
</P>
<P>
   1/4cup pizza sauce
</P>
<P>
   1/2cup pepperoni sausage, chopped
</P>
<P>
   1/4cup green onions, sliced
</P>
<P>
   2ounces mozzarella cheese, shredded
</P>
<P>
   1/2cup red and green bell peppers, chopped
</P>
<P>
   Green pepper, cut into strips for garnish
</P>
<P>
   Pizza dough pieces for dipping
</P>
<P>
   Beat together cream cheese, sour cream, oregano, garlic and
crushed red pepper. Spread evenly in 9-or 10-inch quiche dish or
pie plate.
</P>
<P>
   Spread pizza sauce over top. Sprinkle with pepperoni, green
onion. Bake at 350 degrees for 10 minutes. Top with cheese and bake
5 minutes more or until cheese is melted and mixture is heated
through. Garnish with green pepper strips; serve with baked pizza
dough strips or pita chips. Makes 10-inch quiche pan full.
</P>
<P>
   CINCINNATI BEER-CHEESE DIP
</P>
<P>
   36-ounce rolls sharp cheddar cheese, softened
</P>
<P>
   1 1/2ounces Roquefort or blue cheese
</P>
<P>
   2tablespoons margarine, softened
</P>
<P>
   2medium cloves garlic, minced
</P>
<P>
   1medium onion, chopped
</P>
<P>
   1teaspoon Worcestershire sauce
</P>
<P>
   1/2teaspoon Tabasco sauce
</P>
<P>
   1cup beer, heated and slightly cooled
</P>
<P>
   Rye bread for dipping
</P>
<P>
   Mix cheeses, margarine, onion, garlic, Worcestershire and
Tabasco with electric mixer. Gradually add beer until good
consistency for dipping. Chill.
</P>
<P>
   Hollow out round of rye bread and serve chunks for dipping.
</P>
<P>
   (Above recipes adapted from Internet recipe site:
http://soar.berkeley.edu/recipes/)
</P>
<P>
   JAN TROWER'S SHRIMP SPREAD
</P>
<P>
   110 3/4-ounce can tomato soup
</P>
<P>
   12 1/4-ounce envelope unflavored gelatin
</P>
<P>
   3/4cup water
</P>
<P>
   8ounces cream cheese
</P>
<P>
   1cup finely chopped celery
</P>
<P>
   1/2cup finely chopped green pepper
</P>
<P>
   1/2cup minced onion
</P>
<P>
   1/2teaspoon salt
</P>
<P>
   1cup chopped pecans
</P>
<P>
   2cups chopped, cooked shrimp
</P>
<P>
   1cup mayonnaise
</P>
<P>
   In a medium saucepan, heat soup. In a separate bowl, dissolve
gelatin in water and add to hot soup. Add cream cheese and simmer,
stirring, until smooth. Remove from heat. Allow to cool and add
remaining ingredients.
</P>
<P>
   Put into serving bowl. Refrigerate for at least 6 hours.
</P>
<P>
   Makes about 5 cups.
</P>
<P>
   FETA AND ROSEMARY SPREAD
</P>
<P>
   4ounces feta cheese, crumbled
</P>
<P>
   1tablespoon fresh rosemary, finely chopped
</P>
<P>
   4ounces Neufchatel cheese
</P>
<P>
   2cloves garlic, minced
</P>
<P>
   Place all ingredients in a food processor and pulse until mixed.
Transfer to a bowl; serve with water crackers.
</P>
<P>
   Makes 1 cup.
</P>
<P>
   CRANBERRY CHICKEN SPREAD
</P>
<P>
   3/4cup cubed and shredded chicken
</P>
<P>
   1/4cup cashew pieces
</P>
<P>
   2tablespoons chopped celery
</P>
<P>
   1/2cup mayonnaise
</P>
<P>
   1/4cup sweetened dried cranberries
</P>
<P>
   Combine all ingredients in a medium bowl. Mix and chill well.
</P>
<P>
   Note: Can be used as sandwich spread.
</P>
<P>
   Makes 1 1/4 cups.
</P>
<P>
   (Above recipes adapted from ``Chips , Dips and Salsa'' by Judy
Walker and Kim MacEachern, 1999, Northland Books.)
</P>
<P>
   ANCHOVY SPREAD NO. 2
</P>
<P>
   12chopped anchovy fillets
</P>
<P>
   1tablespoon chopped dill
</P>
<P>
   2tablespoons chopped chives
</P>
<P>
   1cup cream cheese
</P>
<P>
   Chop anchovies very fine and mix with remaining ingredients.
</P>
<P>
   Chill and serve on crackers.
</P>
<P>
   HAM SPREAD NO. 3
</P>
<P>
   1/2pound cold baked ham, finely chopped
</P>
<P>
   1/2cup shredded Swiss cheese
</P>
<P>
   3chopped gherkins
</P>
<P>
   1tablespoon Dijon mustard Mayonnaise to moisten
</P>
<P>
   Mix all ingredients in food processor until just combined; add
enough mayonnaise to make a spread.
</P>
<P>
   (Above two recipes from James Beard's ``Hors d'oeuvre and
Canapes,'' 1985, Quill Books.)
</P>
<P>
   ROASTED GARLIC DIP
</P>
<P>
   110 3/4-ounce can cream of mushroom soup with roasted garlic
</P>
<P>
   113-ounce package cream cheese (low-fat if desired)
</P>
<P>
   118-ounce container sour cream
</P>
<P>
   1/4cup chopped green onions (optional)
</P>
<P>
   1/4cup chopped pecans (optional)
</P>
<P>
   Combine undiluted soup with cream cheese and sour cream. Add
green onions and pecans if desired. Chill and serve from a hollowed
round of pumpernickle or onion bread.
</P>
<P>
   Makes approximately 2 1/2 cups dip.
</P>
