u a BC-TEXASFLAG28-COX     01-27 0343
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-TEXASFLAG28-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Texas official calls removing battle flag `a slippery slope'
 &HT;    By Juan B. Elizondo Jr.
 &HT;    c. 2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   AUSTIN, Texas _ Lt. Gov. Rick Perry says he understands why some
Texans might be offended by the Confederate battle flag, but he
believes it ``represents the heritage.''
</P>
<P>
   ``Like it or not, the Confederacy is part of history, is part of
our heritage,'' Perry told reporters Thursday regarding the flag, a
subject of recent protests nationally and locally. ``We're going to
have this debate, and that's fine. The point is I'm not going to
get my efforts and my energy pulled into that. I'm going to work
with ... the folks who want to be constructive and positive about
how we bring Texans of the 21st century together.''
</P>
<P>
   Gov. George W. Bush and other presidential candidates repeatedly
have been asked whether South Carolina should stop flying the
battle flag. The use of the flag also has been an issue in Hays
County, where Hays High School flies it.
</P>
<P>
   Bush has said South Carolina voters and local Texas voters
should decide whether to display the flag. But the governor has not
said what he believes the flag represents.
</P>
<P>
   ``He recognizes that it evokes different emotions in different
people,'' spokeswoman Linda Edwards said.
</P>
<P>
   Perry said he can see how the flag could be used as a symbol of
hatred, but added that he believes it's a symbol of Texas heritage.
</P>
<P>
   The Texas branch of the National Association for the Advancement
of Colored People this month asked Bush to support efforts to
remove the battle flag from a plaque at the Texas Supreme Court
building, which was built in the 1950s with money from a
long-unused Texas Confederate veterans fund. Edwards said the
governor will respond soon to the request.
</P>
<P>
   Perry said removing the plaque would lead to calls to remove
other monuments and displays that offend other groups.
</P>
<P>
   ``I think you see the slippery slope you get on,'' Perry said.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
</TEXT>
