   SPORTS (``s'' category)
</P>
<P>
   FBN-McNAIR (Atlanta) _ When he came out of tiny Alcorn State
five years ago, he was known as ``Air McNair'' _ the architect of a
record-setting, high-scoring offense that would get the Houston
Oilers franchise back on track. Steve McNair hasn't exactly set the
NFL afire with his statistics, but he has led the Tennessee Titans
to the first Super Bowl in franchise history. By JOHN McCLAIN.
</P>
<P>
   FBN-WARNER (Atlanta) _ Kurt Warner clearly ranks as one of the
most unlikely quarterbacks to start a Super Bowl. After a career
bouncing around the Arena Football League and NFL Europe, Warner
has come out of nowhere to lead the St. Louis Rams to the Super
Bowl. By JODY GOLDSTEIN.
