<TEXT>
<P>
   The Los Angeles Daily News plans to move the following general
stories for use by NYTimes News Service clients, AMs and PMs of
Jan. 28 and thereafter. For questions about stories, contact the
Daily News, (818) 713-3705.
</P>
<P>
   SUPER-ADS -- The whole world will be watching, the nation's best
will be on display, and they all know the entire year is riding on
the Super Bowl this Sunday. And that's just the advertisers. With
the biggest game of the season also being the biggest TV show of
any year, business people know the Super Bowl can be their shot to
launch a new product, or an entirely new company. That gives them
good reason to fork over $2.2 million to ABC for a 30-second spot.
By Steve Carney (Will move on the ``n'' California and ``a''
national news wire.)
</P>
<P>
   X X X
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
