<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-01-27 21:51 </DATE_TIME>
<HEADER>
A8738 &Cx1f; tdt-z
u s BC-FBN-PATRIOTS-KRAFT-BO     01-27 0638
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-FBN-PATRIOTS-KRAFT-BOS </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
FOR ROBERT KARAFT, A FAMILIAR FEELING 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  
 By MICHAEL VEGA  
 c.2000 The Boston Globe  
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   FOXBOROUGH, Mass. _ As he mulled over the price the Patriots
would be willing to pay in order to pry Bill Belichick from the New
York Jets _ most important, a first-round pick in this year's NFL
draft _ owner Robert Kraft said he reached the decision to pull the
trigger on the deal at 10 Wednesday night only after he was
reminded of another tough business decision.
</P>
<P>
   It was the one he made six years ago to buy the Patriots from
James Busch Orthwein for about $180 million.
</P>
<P>
   ``It was the same kind of situation,'' Kraft said during
Belichick's introductory press conference at Foxboro Stadium. ``We
had no shot of getting the team and people were trying to move it
and they wouldn't let us in the process. Then they let us in right
at the end and we paid the highest price ever paid for any
franchise, anywhere in the world, at that time. A lot of people
told me that I was nuts, but in my heart, I knew I was doing the
right thing.''
</P>
<P>
   But there was another motivating factor that compelled Kraft to
return Bill Parcells's phone call Thursday morning and agree to the
Jets' terms, thus setting into motion the chain of events that
culminated with an armistice between the heated AFC East rivals and
Belichick's arrival as the Patriots' new head coach.
</P>
<P>
   ``I thought about the Robert Edwards situation,'' Kraft
admitted, ``and about the uncertainty that we all have with draft
picks.''
</P>
<P>
   Kraft recalled how the Patriots thought they ``had the running
back position solved'' after the club drafted Edwards with their
first-round pick (18th overall) in the 1998 draft. A product from
the University of Georgia, Edwards showed great promise when he
rushed for 1,115 yards, marking the third-best rookie rushing
performance in franchise history.
</P>
<P>
   But any thoughts of gridiron grandeur proved premature when
Edwards suffered a severe knee injury in a freak accident while
participating in a flag football game on the beach during last
year's Pro Bowl activities in Honolulu. Edwards wound up sitting
out all of this season and his future is unclear.
</P>
<P>
   ``What happened, through an act of God, changed all that and
we're still dealing with that now,'' Kraft said. ``I said, here's a
chance to solve our problems with all the positions in the
organization. (Belichick's) someone who gives me peace of mind that
he knows what he's doing and he knows what it takes to win and
that's why we're all in this business.
</P>
<P>
   ``And so, for a No. 1 draft choice, we can bring in a man who I
feel certain will do something rather than with the uncertainty of
the draft pick. So it wasn't even close when I thought about it
(Wednesday) night. That's when I told Bill (Parcells) that we could
do the deal, because we were ready to move in another direction and
make the offer to someone else.''
</P>
<P>
   Kraft declined to say who was next in line for the Patriots, but
it had been widely speculated that Jaguars assistant Dom Capers was
the pick.
</P>
<P>
   ``The most rewarding things in life are very complex and you
have to go through difficult times to enjoy the good times,'' Kraft
said. ``A former head coach said to me that this is not a business
for sane people and I probably have a better understanding of that.
On the other hand, if you persevere and you have a vision of what's
right and you have a collection of good people around you and can
help you get there, then you have a chance to win.
</P>
<P>
   ``And our family is committed to winning. I think Bill Belichick
said it well. We have a good nucleus of players here, our family is
willing to commit the capital to do it, and we will continue to do
it because you have to do that if you want to win.''
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-01-27-00 2151EST &QL; 
</TRAILER>
