A8786 &Cx1f; tad-z
u w BC-UNION-GORE28-COX     01-27 0414
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-UNION-GORE28-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    GORE WINS PRAISE IN CLINTON SPEECH
 &HT;    With UNION. Moving in (w) Washington and (p) politics
categories.
 &HT;    By SCOTT SHEPARD
 &HT;    c.2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   MANCHESTER, N.H. _ President Clinton's State of the Union
address Thursday night heaped praise on Vice President Al Gore and
championed some of the proposals the vice president has advanced in
his presidential campaign.
</P>
<P>
   ``Al Gore is a big part of this presidency,'' explained
Clinton's chief of staff, John Podesta. ``We'll have the biggest
economic expansion in the nation's history. Al Gore is a big part
of that.''
</P>
<P>
   Among those helping to write the speech was Bob Shrum, a White
House consultant who also is one of the vice president's chief
advisers, charged with fashioning the Gore campaign message.
</P>
<P>
   Most significantly in his speech, the president proposed that
``we follow Vice President Gore's suggestion'' to expand federal
programs aimed at expanding health care insurance coverage to
children.
</P>
<P>
   Bill Bradley's sharpest criticism of Gore in the Democratic
primary campaign has been that the vice president's health care
proposal merely ``nibbles at the edges'' of the problem of health
care for children in poverty.
</P>
<P>
   The president also included Gore's proposal to cover
prescription drug costs under the federal Medicare program.
</P>
<P>
   And he saluted Gore's wife, Tipper, for her role in trying to
improve coverage of mental illness.
</P>
<P>
   Clinton also praised Gore's efforts in connecting classrooms to
the Internet, noting the progress in that effort from 3 percent in
1994 to more than 50 percent now.
</P>
<P>
   He also cited Gore's key role as the Senate voted to ``face down
the gun lobby'' in an effort to close loopholes in the sale of
guns, an initiative prompted by the student shooting tragedy at
Columbine High School in Colorado.
</P>
<P>
   He also credited the vice president's role in the
administration's economic and environmental policies.
</P>
<P>
   ``I am grateful for the opportunity the vice president and I
have had to work hard to protect the environment and finally to put
to rest the notion that we can't expand the economy while
protecting the environment,'' he said.
</P>
<P>
   Scott Shepard's e-mail address is scotts(at)coxnews.com
</P>
<P>
   (For in-depth reporting, opinion and cartoonists, visit the Cox
News Campaign 2000 Web site: http://www.coxnews.com/2000.)
</P>
<P>
   ENDIT
</P>
