   The following is the photo list for President Clinton's final
State of the Union speech.
</P>
<P>
   (NYT37) WASHINGTON -- Jan. 27, 2000 -- CLINTON-GORE -- President
Bill Clinton shakes the hand of Vice President Al Gore while
Speaker Dennis Hastert looks on following Clinton's final State of
the Union speech, Thursday. To the delight of Gore's staff and the
irritation of both Bill Bradley and the Republicans, Clinton has,
day after day, announced policies that dovetail with Gore's
presidential campaign effort, and Clinton usually says Gore is the
brains behind them, maybe even the brains behind the White House
generally. (Paul Hosefros/The New York Times)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT36) WASHINGTON -- Jan. 27, 2000 -- CLINTON-SPEECH-6 --
President Bill Clinton leans in the direction of Sen. Strom
Thurmond, R-S.C., while Chief of Staff John Podesta and Secretary
of State Madeleine Albright look on after Clinton delivered his
final State of the Union speech, Thursday. In his speech, Clinton
emphasized ``a 21st-Century American Revolution'' to ensure that
the nation's unprecedented prosperity is shared by all its citizens
-- from pre-schoolers hoping for a head start in education to
seniors in need of medical care. (Paul Hosefros/The New York Times)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT35) WASHINGTON -- Jan. 27, 2000 -- CLINTON-SPEECH-5 --
