<P>
   (NYT33) WASHINGTON -- Jan. 27, 2000 -- CLINTON-SPEECH-3 --
President Bill Clinton delivering his final State of the Union
address, Thursday. Hailing the achievements of his two terms in
office thus far, Clinton began delivering his speech to a joint
session of Congress calling for the American people to launch a
revolution for the 21st century. ``We must shape a 21st century
American revolution, of opportunity, responsibility and community.
We must be, as we were in the beginning, a new nation,'' said
Clinton. (Paul Hosefros/The New York Times)
